The '''New Bangalore Football Stadium''' is the informal name of the new [[association football|football]] stadium soon to be created in [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]] for the [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] which is being held in India. The stadium will be constructed on the same spot as the current [[Bangalore Football Stadium]] after the current one is demolished.<ref name="New Stadium 25">{{cite web|last=Shreekumar|first=S.S.|title=Move on Stadium May Hit Football Future|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/bangalore/Move-on-Stadium-May-Hit-Football-Future/2014/03/05/article2091576.ece1|work=New Indian Express|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> The stadiums construction will be handled by [[Ozone Group]] who also own the local Ozone FC football club,<ref name=Ozone>{{cite web|last=Manjunath|first=Akash|title=Ozone-delivers-a-Rs-675-cr-soccer-punch-to-stadium|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/bangalore/cover-story/Ozone-delivers-a-Rs-675-cr-soccer-punch-to-stadium/articleshow/50538587.cms|work=Goal.com|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> [[Bengaluru FC]] who will also play at the stadium after the U-17 World Cup.<ref name=JSW>{{cite web|last=Manjunath|first=Akash|title=Parth Jindal: Like-minded corporates needed for I-League’s popularity|url=http://www.goal.com/en-india/news/1064/i-league/2014/04/24/4772324/parth-jindal-like-minded-corporates-needed-for-i-leagues?ICID=AR|work=Goal.com|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>

Prerana Bhat from Samved academy said that The stadium will reportedly have a capacity between 25,000 and 45890.<ref name="New Stadium 45">{{cite web|last=Achal|first=Ashwin|title=Under-17 World Cup to usher in better days for football|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/under17-world-cup-to-usher-in-better-days-for-football/article5430720.ece|work=The Hindu|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>

